# Golden conformance artifacts are byte-exact: no EOL conversion, ever.
# (GoldenTraceTest compares committed bytes against regenerated ones; a CRLF checkout would
# fail every comparison on Windows.)
* -text

# The golden media the projects play (see golden/make-golden-media.cpp). `binary` is -text -diff:
# no EOL conversion, and no attempt to render a WAV or a SoundFont as a text diff.
golden/*.wav binary
golden/*.sf2 binary

# The D2 PNG decode fixtures (tools/ptdecode). Same reason: raw bytes with 0x0A inside pixel data
# that core.autocrlf would rewrite, and nothing to gain from a text diff of a PNG. `* -text` above
# already blocks the EOL conversion; this adds -diff and states the intent by name.
images/*.png binary
